<subSubSection id="78438B984AE3E501E41F34E928BCFB61" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DD7DBC7531922F4D621DC0ECE52791CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5296EA8E7962BA7D7F52376171D558FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">A small narrow species with a long head, pronotum with two long, weakly converging raised ridges, forewing with extra crossveins but only weakly reticulate. Aedeagus of male in lateral view with gradually recurved basiventral process.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E35CE2A6E1A81D28A609E44977AC723" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="materials_examined">
