sp., nymph, from 
<normalizedToken id="28C881838F49854489B99CA1302ACCF8" originalValue="Mérida">Merida</normalizedToken>
, Venezuela (courtesy of D. Takiya) 
<emphasis id="5293B4582EF22F6E0E95E9B2A885B1F8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">6-12</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="DF0997A28D8D51503F0678A55DAA16FF" authorityName="McKamey" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Diestostemma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diestostemma bicristata" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristata">
<emphasis id="ABE67D397CB6448969A5F673E252F033" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diestostemma bicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sp. nov., holotype 
<emphasis id="CD08BC710DECF072ACAE4650394C9914" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">6</emphasis>
head and partial thorax, ventroanterior view 
<emphasis id="03AD4A324634C0E3B5B8E86D37AE320E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">7</emphasis>
head and pronotum, dorsoanterior view 
<emphasis id="D714D7C869BC58328AEBBB12E8941B7D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">8</emphasis>
connective and styles, dorsal view 
